Are you kidding me? This video isn't meaningless, at all. The way i interpret it is the mime dancer, he is everyone of us, following the light (aka Madari- in this context, God). He tries to break away from it often but eventually follows it. 

The knife-juggler-person (idk what they are called really) is growing old and is now losing his skills, a commentary on aging which is also referenced in the song several times. 

For the final act, the person risks his daughter's life for the sake of the show and plays into luck. In this act, his fate is entirely under God's will, making him the ultimate Jammura. 

Sure, they could've made a 7 minute video w the full arrangement, and added even more depth to it, but hey, don't denounce artistic videos like this. It's because of these discouraging comments that the Indian music industry doesn't experiment with deeper ideas even if they can. Peace.
